&lt;div id="outline-container-org22b8cfe" class="outline-3"&gt;
&lt;h3 id="org22b8cfe"&gt;Rule Generalisation #2 (Alternative)&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org22b8cfe"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
The rules as written could also be interpreted as follows
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
When players tie for a place, they all get points for the next lower place.
Players scoring lower also drop to the next place.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
This rule can be applied recursively, starting from the first place.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
There are only minor differences compared to the first version, namely when
there the first three players are tied.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;
I've enumerated all combinations in the table below.
